abstract: Japan agrees to return royal documents to South Korea that were looted during Japanese rule of Korean Peninsula from 1910 to 1945.
snippet: Japan’s prime minister will return looted Korean royal documents during a summit meeting with his South Korean counterpart this week, officials said Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Japan’s prime minister will return looted Korean royal documents during a summit meeting with his South Korean counterpart this week, officials said Tuesday.

headline.main: South Korea: Japan to Return Looted Korean Royal Documents
